// SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0 WITH LLVM-exception
//
// test/audited/turboV_iverilog.test — M7 US4 cell for
// (turboV × iverilog). Phase 6 scaffold.
//
// turboV is a full RISC-V CPU. Its golden source is the vendored
// upstream Python reference simulator at
// `test/audited/turboV/simulator/ref_sim.py` (per FR-017 +
// research.md §9). The audited regression compiles+runs an
// instruction-stream test binary under iverilog and compares the
// captured VCD against the reference simulator's hand-traced
// golden.

// REQUIRES: iverilog

// 1. Emit Verilog from the turboV core sources. The CMakeLists.txt
//    inside the project organizes the source list; here we
//    extract the top-level via the project's src/core/turboV.nsl.
// RUN: rm -rf %t-verilog && mkdir -p %t-verilog
// RUN: %nslc -emit=verilog %S/turboV/src/core/turboV.nsl -o %t-verilog/

// 2. Compile + simulate one of the instruction-family scenarios.
//    The add scenario uses the vendored
//    tests/csr_inst_test/crt0.S etc as the instruction stream.
//    (Phase 5 T068 lands the actual scenario + binary build flow.)
// RUN: iverilog -g2012 -o %t.vvp %t-verilog/*.v \
// RUN:   %S/turboV/src/integration/clint.nsl \
// RUN:   %S/turboV/src/integration/ram64x8K.nsl \
// RUN:   %S/turboV/src/integration/rom64x2K.nsl \
// RUN:   %S/turboV/src/integration/uart.nsl
// RUN: cd %T && vvp %t.vvp +VCDFILE=%t.vcd

// 3. Compare against the golden produced by the vendored Python
//    reference simulator.
// RUN: %vcd-diff %S/turboV/golden/add.vcd %t.vcd
